Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_sai_boundary_flops(25.10)                    add_sai_boundary_flops(25.10)

Name
       add_sai_boundary_flops

Syntax
       add_sai_boundary_flops

       [-help]

       [-clock <string>]

       [-delete_flops]

       -hinsts <string>

       -ports <string>

       [-ref_flop <string> [-clock_input_pin <string>]

       [-data_input_pin <string>]

       [-data_output_pin <string>]]

       Allows  insertion  of boundary flops for empty modules/blocks. The com-
       mand options specify the clock net name, the module name and the module
       pin name.

Parameters
       -clock <string>
              Specifies clock net name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -clock_input_pin <string>
              Specifies the cell CLK port name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -data_input_pin <string>
              Specifies the cell D port name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -data_output_pin <string>
              Specifies the cell Q port name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -delete_flops
              Removes all the flops that have been added.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each add_sai_boundary_flops parameter.

       -hinsts <string>
              Specifies the module name.

              Note:  While  specifying multiple hinsts and multiple ports, en-
              sure that the number of specified hinsts is the same as the num-
              ber of specified ports.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ports <string>
              Specifies the module pin name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ref_flop <string>
              Specifies the flop cell name to be inserted along the boundary.

              Data_type: string, optional

